being interrogated.

506
00:41:58,250 --> 00:42:00,161
They used an electric prod on him.

507
00:42:00,292 --> 00:42:02,874
They half-drowned him
in a swimming pool.

508
00:42:03,500 --> 00:42:06,162
But what can you do?
They had this motto -

509
00:42:06,292 --> 00:42:08,123
"No blood, no foul."

510
00:42:09,167 --> 00:42:11,158
What does that mean?

511
00:42:11,292 --> 00:42:14,079
Means if they don't fuckin' bleed,
you've done nothing wrong.

512
00:42:15,250 --> 00:42:17,241
- Want another drink?
- Yeah.

513
00:42:21,875 --> 00:42:25,197
Hi, love. Pint of lager
and a vodka and tonic, please.

514
00:42:31,667 --> 00:42:33,783
Room clear! One bravo!

515
00:42:34,833 --> 00:42:36,949
Move away! Tell them.

516
00:42:37,083 --> 00:42:40,450
Stand away! Move out the fucking way.

517
00:42:41,708 --> 00:42:43,915
Come on, let's get that kid out!

518
00:42:47,167 --> 00:42:49,749
- Get the kid.
- He's taking too long!

519
00:42:51,292 --> 00:42:54,079
- Get out!
- Get out the way, I'll get him.

520
00:42:54,208 --> 00:42:56,244
Get outside,
you stupid fuckin' rag-head!

521
00:42:57,417 --> 00:43:01,490
They had this orchard. They wouldn't
give any information, right?

522
00:43:01,625 --> 00:43:05,447
So the Americans threatened them,
to flatten the orchard.

523
00:43:06,625 --> 00:43:11,665
So this woman, she's fuckin'
hangin' on to this tree,

524
00:43:11,792 --> 00:43:14,329
cos that's her fuckin' life.

525
00:43:14,458 --> 00:43:18,531
She's holding on to this tree.
She's not gonna move.

526
00:43:18,667 --> 00:43:22,239
So they order this young soldier -
young black kid -

527
00:43:22,375 --> 00:43:24,957
to go in, get her out.

528
00:43:25,083 --> 00:43:28,405
But he's nearly fuckin' breaking
her arm, she's struggling so much.

529
00:43:28,542 --> 00:43:32,455
The fucking tanks go in,
roots get torn up...

530
00:43:33,083 --> 00:43:36,746
This kid's standing there,
he's trying hide his tears.

531
00:43:39,125 --> 00:43:42,117
And the thing that got me
more than anything is...

532
00:43:42,250 --> 00:43:45,322
they're fuckin' playing jazz music
on the speakers.

533
00:43:46,792 --> 00:43:48,908
On the tanks, there's jazz music.

534
00:43:50,875 --> 00:43:54,697
So I left. I got out the Residents,
that was it.

535
00:43:57,708 --> 00:43:59,994
But you didn't get out, did you?

536
00:44:00,125 --> 00:44:01,706
You joined up with Haynes.

537
00:44:02,750 --> 00:44:05,207
- You were still there.
- Because Haynes...

538
00:44:05,333 --> 00:44:08,040
It was me last chance...
at a big payday.

539
00:44:08,167 --> 00:44:12,285
Why did you go on your own,
if it were that good?

540
00:44:12,417 --> 00:44:16,035
Cos I wanted my own firm.

541
00:44:16,167 --> 00:44:18,704
I wanted a piece for meself.
And why not?

542
00:44:18,833 --> 00:44:22,155
And you know what?
Haynes was fucking furious.

543
00:44:22,292 --> 00:44:25,364
He couldn't get it in his head,
how a scruff like me -

544
00:44:25,500 --> 00:44:28,207
from fuckin' here - a scruff like me,

545
00:44:28,333 --> 00:44:31,120
had an eye for the fuckin'
main chance, as fast as him.

546
00:44:37,625 --> 00:44:39,286
What happened, Fergus?

547
00:44:46,458 --> 00:44:50,497
I lost three of my lads
in an ambush. Good lads.

548
00:44:52,083 --> 00:44:54,290
Got the client out. The golden rule -

549
00:44:54,417 --> 00:44:56,954
"The package always comes first."

550
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:01,412
I left the lads behind.

551
00:45:01,542 --> 00:45:03,874
We never did that in the army.

552
00:45:04,875 --> 00:45:09,073
I thought I was OK, then I got
a letter from one of the mothers.

553
00:45:13,083 --> 00:45:15,244
Things just started falling apart.

554
00:46:21,292 --> 00:46:22,782
Slap me.

555
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:25,911
Come on, Rachel. Slap me.

556
00:46:26,417 --> 00:46:28,373
Come on.

557
00:46:32,208 --> 00:46:33,414
Harder.

558
00:46:34,792 --> 00:46:35,872
Harder.

559
00:46:46,583 --> 00:46:48,949
Punch me.

560
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:17,286
I was in the archives. Donald came in.

561
00:48:17,417 --> 00:48:20,580
- I had to drop it.
- He's still out there, is he?

562
00:48:20,708 --> 00:48:22,619
Aye, he's a fuckin' arse.

563
00:48:22,750 --> 00:48:26,993
Well listen...
did you manage to get anything?

564
00:48:28,625 --> 00:48:31,332
The first of September,
tell me what you found.

565
00:48:33,333 --> 00:48:35,824
Well, there's nothing happened,
by all accounts.

566
00:48:35,958 --> 00:48:39,405
"There's nothing fuckin' happened"?
They shot up a fuckin' taxi!

567
00:48:39,542 --> 00:48:42,705
Well, there's fuck all
in the record about it,

568
00:48:42,833 --> 00:48:44,619
cos I've checked everything.

569
00:48:44,750 --> 00:48:46,206
So...

570
00:48:46,333 --> 00:48:50,155
Did you find out who was
on duty with Frankie that day?

571
00:48:50,292 --> 00:48:53,659
- Nelson.
- Nelson? Well, that ties up.

572
00:48:54,250 --> 00:48:56,741
And three Colombian guys, as well.

573
00:48:56,875 --> 00:48:59,992
Three Colombian guys?
Did you get their names?

574
00:49:00,125 --> 00:49:01,865
Nah, never heard of them.

575
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:06,164
Look, I need you to get
the fuckin' names, mate.

576
00:49:06,292 --> 00:49:09,784
Just get them, and text me with them
as soon as you've got them.

577
00:49:10,875 --> 00:49:13,207
What about Jamie? Any word on Jamie?

578
00:49:13,333 --> 00:49:17,406
He's in Afghanistan, up some
fuckin' mountain, fixing Jeeps.

579
00:49:17,542 --> 00:49:18,367
- For fuck's sake.
- Look,

580
00:49:18,396 --> 00:49:20,534
I'll try to get a message to him.

581
00:49:20,667 --> 00:49:22,248
Best I can do, man.

582
00:49:22,375 --> 00:49:25,617
I appreciate your help,
and I won't forget this.

583
00:49:25,750 --> 00:49:27,331
I won't forget.

584
00:49:27,458 --> 00:49:31,326
Right, see you later.

585
00:49:31,458 --> 00:49:33,119
Who was that?

586
00:49:34,958 --> 00:49:37,916
Tommy, a contractor in Baghdad.

587
00:49:38,042 --> 00:49:39,828
Who's Jamie?

588
00:49:39,958 --> 00:49:43,997
Jamie's an old mate from army days.
A mechanic.

589
00:49:44,125 --> 00:49:48,869
And what did you mean, when you said
someone shot up a taxi?

590
00:49:49,000 --> 00:49:50,490
Look...

591
00:49:52,208 --> 00:49:56,030
Something happened out there.
Something really bad.

592
00:49:57,167 --> 00:50:01,115
First of September,
two weeks before Frankie died.

593
00:50:03,167 --> 00:50:06,159
There's someone I want you to meet.
An Iraqi musician.

594
00:50:06,292 --> 00:50:09,329
Has it got something to do with Frankie?

595
00:50:09,458 --> 00:50:11,619
I want to know
what's going on, Fergus.

596
00:50:13,083 --> 00:50:14,698
I don't know, myself.

597
00:50:14,833 --> 00:50:17,165
But I tell you what,
I'm going to find out.

598
00:50:19,875 --> 00:50:22,457
This song is from Mesopotamia -

599
00:50:22,583 --> 00:50:25,370
which means
"The land between the two rivers" -

600
00:50:25,500 --> 00:50:28,082
the Tigris and the Euphrates,

601
00:50:28,208 --> 00:50:31,496
where the homo sapiens
learned to write, to count,

602
00:50:31,625 --> 00:50:33,081
and mark the stars.

603
00:50:33,208 --> 00:50:37,201
Which anthropologists call
"The Cradle of Civilisations".

604
00:50:38,208 --> 00:50:41,871
In my dreams, it may be once again.

605
00:52:19,042 --> 00:52:23,035
That's one of the children,
shouting Taif's name.

606
00:52:24,250 --> 00:52:26,115
"Taif is somewhere, here."

607
00:52:32,292 --> 00:52:33,907
Oh, Frankie.

608
00:52:38,542 --> 00:52:40,533
You've killed a family!

609
00:52:40,958 --> 00:52:43,620
- Nelson, you stupid bastard!
- They're all dead.

610
00:52:43,750 --> 00:52:45,536
You've killed a fuckin' family!

611
00:52:45,667 --> 00:52:48,625
Frank, get back in the fucking van!

612
00:52:48,750 --> 00:52:51,787
You've killed a fucking family!

613
00:52:55,750 --> 00:52:58,662
Fucking get in the van. Get in!

614
00:52:58,792 --> 00:53:00,623
Fuck's sake...

615
00:53:01,042 --> 00:53:02,907
Just get in!

616
00:53:11,417 --> 00:53:13,954
There are several messages
you should hear, as well.

617
00:53:17,708 --> 00:53:22,407
"Taif. Ranj.
Answer me please. Where are you?

618
00:53:22,542 --> 00:53:25,614
"Why you went out? You didn't tell me.

619
00:53:25,750 --> 00:53:29,038
"Who's listening to me?
Where are you now?

620
00:53:29,583 --> 00:53:32,575
"I don't have anything else
without them.

621
00:53:34,208 --> 00:53:37,450
"Please, they're both clever boys,
they haven't done anyone.

622
00:53:37,583 --> 00:53:40,655
"Please, don't touch my boys.

623
00:53:40,792 --> 00:53:42,703
"I'll be your servant.

624
00:53:42,833 --> 00:53:47,327
"I'll sell my car, I'll sell my house,
give you anything you ask me."

625
00:53:57,958 --> 00:54:00,950
"They are only my sons,
they are my only sons."

626
00:54:06,042 --> 00:54:08,033
Rachel!

627
00:54:09,583 --> 00:54:11,039
Rachel.

628
00:54:12,625 --> 00:54:14,206
Rachel, wait.

629
00:54:20,083 --> 00:54:21,698
Rachel!

630
00:54:21,833 --> 00:54:24,745
Look, you don't understand.

631
00:54:26,750 --> 00:54:28,115
Look at Craig -

632
00:54:28,250 --> 00:54:32,038
ordered to shoot, hesitates cos
he think she's seen a kid in the car.

633
00:54:32,167 --> 00:54:35,614
Bang! Blinded for life.
What about Jason?

634
00:54:35,750 --> 00:54:37,286
No fucking legs!

635
00:54:37,417 --> 00:54:39,908
Half a gut, can't even wipe
his own fuckin' arse!

636
00:54:40,042 --> 00:54:42,124
It's split-second decisions.

637
00:54:42,250 --> 00:54:44,912
- You saw that film!
- It's fuckin" us or them!

638
00:54:45,042 --> 00:54:46,703
What about that little boy?

639
00:54:46,833 --> 00:54:48,869
He had a mobile, he didn't have a gun.

640
00:54:49,000 --> 00:54:52,117
Oh, come on! What d'you think
they use to set off the I EDs?

641
00:54:52,250 --> 00:54:55,663
- I don't even know what an IED is!
- Improvised explosive device.

642
00:54:55,792 --> 00:54:59,614
It's been fucking killing our lads
for the last three years.

643
00:55:00,875 --> 00:55:03,366
Come on, Rachel. Fucking wake up.

644
00:55:07,750 --> 00:55:11,038
Why wasn't there an incident report?
At least four people were killed.

645
00:55:11,167 --> 00:55:14,534
To avoid a scandal. They don't
want to get a reputation as cowboys.

646
00:55:14,667 --> 00:55:16,999
That could jeopardise
millions' worth of contracts.

647
00:55:17,125 --> 00:55:19,161
And what about
those poor people in the taxi?

648
00:55:19,292 --> 00:55:21,658
Come on, there's over
a million people dead.

649
00:55:21,792 --> 00:55:27,332
You think they'd give a flying fuck
about a taxi driver and a nosy kid?

650
00:55:27,458 --> 00:55:29,494
Frankie did. He cared.

651
00:55:31,125 --> 00:55:34,413
It's a text message from Tommy.

652
00:55:34,542 --> 00:55:37,284
The names of the Colombians
that were on duty with Frankie,

653
00:55:37,417 --> 00:55:39,658
the day they shot up the taxi.

654
00:55:39,792 --> 00:55:41,328
Show me.

655
00:55:46,667 --> 00:55:48,498
It's the same names.

656
00:55:49,583 --> 00:55:52,871
The same three boys that were killed
on the 17th, with Frankie.

657
00:55:54,292 --> 00:55:56,578
- You sure about that?
- Yeah.

658
00:55:56,708 --> 00:55:58,573
Haynes sent them to me.

659
00:56:00,458 --> 00:56:03,165
Fuck. That makes Nelson
the only survivor.

660
00:56:04,208 --> 00:56:06,790
- Was it him who shot up the taxi?
- Yeah.

661
00:56:07,917 --> 00:56:10,659
I was in the Paras with him,
he's a fuckin' arsehole.

662
00:56:10,792 --> 00:56:12,248
I'm going to the police.

663
00:56:12,375 --> 00:56:15,867
Wait! What are the police
gonna do in Baghdad?

664
00:56:16,000 --> 00:56:17,740
These bastards will run rings round them.

665
00:56:17,875 --> 00:56:21,697
I don't give a shit. I'll go
to the police, the MP, the papers...

666
00:56:21,833 --> 00:56:24,495
Just stop. Wait a minute.

667
00:56:24,625 --> 00:56:27,947
Remember the Iraqi that was
picked up by the soldiers in Basra?

668
00:56:28,083 --> 00:56:29,414
Eh?

669
00:56:29,542 --> 00:56:33,330
93 injuries, beaten to death -
they still got off with it!

670
00:56:33,458 --> 00:56:36,825
They closed ranks -
they always have, they always will.

671
00:56:39,042 --> 00:56:41,158
- What can we do?
- Give me more time.

672
00:56:41,292 --> 00:56:43,829
Just give me some more time.

673
00:56:48,917 --> 00:56:50,999
Fergus.

674
00:56:51,125 --> 00:56:55,448
At the funeral, Walker asked me
about an Iraqi mobile.

675
00:56:55,583 --> 00:56:58,450
He said Frankie had borrowed
an Iraqi mobile phone,

676
00:56:58,583 --> 00:57:00,574
and he'd forgotten to return it.

677
00:57:05,167 --> 00:57:07,249
Fuckin' bastard knew all along.

678
00:57:20,417 --> 00:57:23,989
- Think he's going to turn up?
- I know he will. Don't ask why.

679
00:57:26,625 --> 00:57:28,456
Put that one on silent.

680
00:57:34,917 --> 00:57:36,407
Is it working?

681
00:57:36,542 --> 00:57:38,533
Yeah, you're ringing me now.

682
00:57:40,167 --> 00:57:42,249
I'll hide that in his car.

683
00:57:42,375 --> 00:57:44,036
Put mine on mute.

684
00:57:45,167 --> 00:57:47,783
Sometimes the simplest things
work better.

685
00:57:50,583 --> 00:57:51,743
What's that?

686
00:57:53,000 --> 00:57:54,911
It's a tracking device.

687
00:57:55,042 --> 00:57:58,330
Nothing fancy,
you just buy it over the counter.

688
00:58:04,750 --> 00:58:06,615
There he is.

689
00:59:02,708 --> 00:59:06,030
I mean, this taxi
just got way too close.

690
00:59:07,542 --> 00:59:12,332
Our wagon carried out manoeuvres
right down to the letter.

691
00:59:12,458 --> 00:59:14,915
They went from the outside lane
down to the inside lane.

692
00:59:15,042 --> 00:59:16,703
Taxi's still coming.

693
00:59:16,833 --> 00:59:18,994
They tried to pull away from the taxi.

694
00:59:19,125 --> 00:59:20,706
Taxi was still on his tail.

695
00:59:21,542 --> 00:59:24,158
One of the Colombian boys
started screaming at Nelson

696
00:59:24,292 --> 00:59:26,283
to take a warning shot.

697
00:59:26,417 --> 00:59:29,284
Nelson fired a mini-flare.
Taxi kept coming.

698
00:59:29,417 --> 00:59:32,909
Nelson fired a shot.
Taxi didn't pull back.

699
00:59:33,042 --> 00:59:36,205
Nelson had no option -
he took the taxi out.

700
00:59:37,417 --> 00:59:39,499
What about Frankie?

701
00:59:41,042 --> 00:59:43,704
Well, Frankie forced the driver
to stop the vehicle.

702
00:59:43,833 --> 00:59:45,414
Run back to the taxi.

703
00:59:45,542 --> 00:59:48,864
He put his own life at risk,
and the entire team's.

704
00:59:49,000 --> 00:59:50,956
Nelson wanted him sacked.

705
00:59:52,542 --> 00:59:54,282
What did you do?

706
01:00:01,333 --> 01:00:03,540
I'm risking my career here.

707
01:00:04,583 --> 01:00:07,370
I should've went through the channels...

708
01:00:07,500 --> 01:00:09,741
but Frankie was beside himself.

709
01:00:09,875 --> 01:00:12,412
Especially about the kids.

710
01:00:12,542 --> 01:00:15,079
He suggested compensation.

711
01:00:15,208 --> 01:00:19,201
We all agreed. We all chipped in,
and we told no one outside of Iraq.

712
01:00:20,083 --> 01:00:23,200
- Did he phone you that night?
- Yeah, he did.

713
01:00:24,250 --> 01:00:26,491
I phoned my wife, too.

714
01:00:28,458 --> 01:00:31,291
I went with Hakim,

715
01:00:31,417 --> 01:00:35,205
found the taxi driver's family,
paid 'em in cash.

716
01:00:35,333 --> 01:00:39,747
Found the other people's family...
Hakim organised it all.

717
01:00:39,875 --> 01:00:41,957
Maybe you should talk to him first.

718
01:00:47,250 --> 01:00:50,242
Hello, it's Walker.
I'm in the UK with Fergus.

719
01:00:50,375 --> 01:00:54,243
Fergus Molloy.
He's got a few questions for you.

720
01:00:57,458 --> 01:00:58,823
Hakim?

721
01:01:03,000 --> 01:01:05,616
Have you got a photo
of Frankie's vehicle?

722
01:01:06,833 --> 01:01:08,824
I do.

723
01:01:11,708 --> 01:01:13,744
We had it towed back to base.

724
01:01:21,417 --> 01:01:23,954
It's true. They paid the families.

725
01:01:25,000 --> 01:01:27,742
Frankie was too good for Iraq, Rachel.

726
01:01:34,833 --> 01:01:37,370
I've just left them.

727
01:01:40,625 --> 01:01:44,072
I think it was OK.
She believed me, that's for sure.

728
01:01:47,417 --> 01:01:51,956
No, he wasn 't drinking.
Mineral water, the whole time.

729
01:01:52,083 --> 01:01:56,622
Well, he spoke to Hakim.
That was a good fuckin' idea.

730
01:01:56,750 --> 01:02:00,572
I don't think they've got the mobile,
or they would've asked more questions.

731
01:02:00,708 --> 01:02:04,451
It's best if he gets done and they send
him to prison for a couple of years.

732
01:02:08,583 --> 01:02:12,451
Have they given
the green light for the takeover yet?

733
01:02:12,583 --> 01:02:14,869
That's ex cellent, Andy.

734
01:02:15,000 --> 01:02:18,538
It's all about you and your contracts.
You know that, don 't you?

735
01:02:18,667 --> 01:02:21,784
Listen, we'll open a couple
of bottles when we meet, yeah?

736
01:02:21,917 --> 01:02:22,997
Take care.

737
01:02:23,125 --> 01:02:25,867
- They're bastards, Fergus.
- Too fuckin' right, they are.

738
01:02:32,208 --> 01:02:34,369
- Peggy.
- Who's Peggy?

739
01:02:35,250 --> 01:02:37,491
She's got a bar
in the Green Zone in Baghdad.

740
01:02:37,625 --> 01:02:39,866
She's got some information.

741
01:02:40,875 --> 01:02:45,790
Nelson was smashed.
